- NO-ASSUMPTION PRINCIPLE: take UserInputsRequired.MissingInformation action when the previous ActionResults present multiple choices and user has not stated preference or priority. DO NOT make assumptions on preference or priority for critical options/decisions (location, time, genre, flavor, style, color, shape, size, skill level, etc.).
